<heading id="B3088105FF82FFFEFE081FC986C6B7D4" box="[401,914,1476,1503]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="21" pageNumber="820" reason="5">
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF82FFFEFE081FC986C6B7D4" authority="(Fabricius, 1775)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[401,914,1476,1503]" class="Insecta" family="Libellulidae" genus="Orthemis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="21" pageNumber="820" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferruginea">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF82FFFEFE081FC98752B7D4" bold="true" box="[401,518,1476,1503]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="820">Orthemis</emphasis>
aff. 
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF82FFFEFDA51FC98796B7D4" bold="true" box="[572,706,1476,1503]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="820">ferruginea</emphasis>
(Fabricius, 1775)
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8403669FF82FFFDFF591FF7877DB2C1" blockId="21.[160,1156,1530,1728]" lastBlockId="22.[160,1156,142,202]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="821" pageId="21" pageNumber="820">
The dragonfly 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF82FFFEFEF01FF78772B418" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[361,550,1530,1555]" class="Insecta" family="Libellulidae" genus="Orthemis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="21" pageNumber="820" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferruginea">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF82FFFEFEF01FF7842FB418" box="[361,379,1530,1555]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="820">O</emphasis>
. aff. 
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF82FFFEFE2E1FF78772B418" box="[439,550,1530,1555]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="820">ferruginea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the normal form in that it is red-violet. 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF82FFFEFF391C108406B43D" author="Donnelly N" box="[160,338,1565,1590]" pageId="21" pageNumber="820" pagination="7 - 9" refId="ref24517" refString="Donnelly N. 2002. Odonata of St. Thomas and St. John, Virgin Islands. Argia. 14 (1): 7 - 9." type="journal article" year="2002">Donnelly (2002)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF82FFFEFE101C108724B43D" author="Garrison RW &amp; Von Ellenrieder N &amp; Louton JA" box="[393,624,1565,1590]" pageId="21" pageNumber="820" refId="ref25047" refString="Garrison RW, Von Ellenrieder N, Louton JA. 2006. Dragonfly genera of the New World; an illustrated and annotated key to the Anisoptera. Baltimore (USA): John Hopkins University Press; p. 368." type="journal volume" year="2006">Garrison et al. (2006)</bibRefCitation>
suggest that it may be an undescribed species. We suspect this is the species 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF82FFFEFE611C32878AB453" author="Ramirez A &amp; Maldonado-Benitez N &amp; Mariani-Rios A &amp; Figueroa-Santiago J" box="[504,734,1599,1624]" pageId="21" pageNumber="820" pagination="9711" refId="ref28863" refString="Ramirez A, Maldonado-Benitez N, Mariani-Rios A, Figueroa-Santiago J. 2020. Dragonflies and damselflies (Odonata) from Puerto Rico: a checklist with notes on distribution and habitat. PeerJ. 8: e 9711. doi: 10.7717 / peerj. 9711." type="journal article" year="2020">Ramírez et al. (2020)</bibRefCitation>
refer to as 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF82FFFEFCF91C328697B453" authority="Antillean" authorityName="Hagen" authorityYear="1861" box="[864,963,1599,1624]" class="Insecta" family="Libellulidae" genus="Orthemis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="21" pageNumber="820" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF82FFFEFCF91C328697B453" box="[864,963,1599,1624]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="820">Orthemis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
‘Antillean red’ in their text. This libellulid was very common, and we found it on St. Thomas at nearly every water body, lentic and lotic. Nymphs were always found in ponds, but adults were seen cruising ghuts, ponds (including ornamental ponds), open fields, golf courses, roads, and around the St. Thomas airport. 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF81FFFDFD951A838794B2AC" author="Donnelly N" box="[524,704,142,167]" pageId="22" pageNumber="821" pagination="7 - 9" refId="ref24517" refString="Donnelly N. 2002. Odonata of St. Thomas and St. John, Virgin Islands. Argia. 14 (1): 7 - 9." type="journal article" year="2002">Donnelly (2002)</bibRefCitation>
consolidated records from St. Thomas, St. John, 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FF81FFFDFE9F1ABC840CB2C1" box="[262,344,177,202]" name="British Virgin Islands" pageId="22" pageNumber="821">Tortola</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FF81FFFDFE0D1ABC8771B2C1" box="[404,549,177,202]" name="British Virgin Islands" pageId="22" pageNumber="821">Virgin Gorda</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
